// engine-010-history — `history` attribute on a composite state-child (§51.0.N).
//
// Demonstrates A5-7 history surface (S67 amendment, SPEC §51.0.N) — a bare
// `history` attribute on a composite state-child instructs the compiler to
// synthesize a reactive cell that stores the inner engine's last-active
// variant on outer-exit, and restores from that cell on outer-re-entry.
//
// Target form `.Variant.history` (§51.0.N): used wherever `.Variant` is legal
// as a `rule=` target or as the right-hand side of an engine-variable write,
// to mean "transition AND restore inner from history" (vs bare `.Variant`
// which starts the inner at its initial=).
//
// `history` is legal ONLY on composite state-children (those whose body
// contains a nested <engine>). On a non-composite state-child the typer fires
// E-HISTORY-NO-INNER-ENGINE per §34. Shallow only this revision per
// OQ-Harel-4 — deep history is deferred.
//
// v1 implementation state (2026-05-11):
//   - Parser captures `historyAttr: true` (engine-statechild-parser.ts).
//   - Parser captures `.Variant.history` as `historyForm: true` on rule entries.
//   - Typer (SYM PASS 11) fires E-HISTORY-NO-INNER-ENGINE on non-composite.
//   - Codegen flattens `.X.history` to base variant "X" today
//     (emit-engine.ts:532 — Wave 4 follow-on for synth-cell write/read).
//   - Tree-shake intent (§51.0.N): when no engine declares `history`, the
//     usage-analyzer's `engineHistory` flag remains false; synth-cell
//     emission code path is elided.
//
// This sample exists to ensure the canonical history shape parses + type-
// checks clean and to be the surface adopters reach for. Reading the
// emitted `__scrml_engine_appMode_transitions` shows the table currently
// flattens `.Playing.history → "Playing"` (Wave 4 follow-on).

<program>
${
    type AppMode:enum  = { Title, Playing, Paused }
    type PlayMode:enum = { Exploring, Battle, Inventory }
}

<engine for=AppMode initial=.Title>
    <Title rule=.Playing></>

    <Playing history rule=(.Title | .Paused)>
        <engine for=PlayMode initial=.Exploring>
            <Exploring rule=.Battle></>
            <Battle rule=.Exploring></>
            <Inventory></>
        </>
    </>

    <Paused rule=.Playing.history></>
</>

<div class="game">
    <h1>App: ${@appMode.variant}</>
    <button onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Playing}>Start</>
    <button onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Paused}>Pause</>
    <button onclick=${@appMode = AppMode.Title}>Quit</>
</div>
</program>
